[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Inspecting Android accessors**\n\nI'm considering whether the `testRuntimeOnly android-libcore-memory.jar` influences `UnsafeUtil` to select Android accessors. I notice the JVM test warning might be relevant here. It seems that Android accessors are using `Field.get(null)` without `setAccessible`, which could lead to private fields returning null. I wonder about the existing `javalite` generated holders being private fields as well. Is `Struct FieldsDefaultEntryHolder defaultEntry` perhaps static final and package-private? I think I need to inspect the source code to find out more.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0e1eab49fa8bc245016a24e12828488193b6ac7927cd6ac091\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJOErt-krsNXIO3lHn44ysb7tMeyOFilNQVmjwp_icy30HMAiVkChxnhgqROeeGAZilrThtGlNfrM3tJ6l58jj-5xcDIZqmREiLuZfNjMrQEg4EaxcS3ib-2qzp6uiShCGVfpmx4XeKNl-RUmffQa8-NJoiVKoTutf1PAcswCirC5_fcL3zqqoVZyM5ft6MajkhF5ugCdl7JH0XDn_wZe5_hzthu33v6rQfPKfXCYoBjJ0sETuRNCc_04WZc1CZlxmgNbdYZ3NiWVRGyFF3YzbjicrwVYoIum9P1aGdnrcWTXN8mFzzjvoqBwZ6WLzlZC2vlJYq7yV8EoWAbzLLj5M6aDEv7i3zDMtenSt-pi1T-FWEQJp6X3z3TMwmffwkfCvCgcGDsG-whS5Of5tLuOryuWqcPC4JYIWlHnty2moA3KTEilXl87OJEcT3X9LuBoC5KsCvxPP6l5lEp7HCScpJT_Wr_AxZxbP4os7Eq1yt5sYl52c-OICOTwwvep3pnDMktVT7echfR5f7CUjfCpBzoqfGK1cxZLufkXwDUf_HsM4ulK4GjRp1_UciPwpkLeQ1cOd-dhLjiez5y4ivjZLBLE6Vc3iLgCD0XGGsu5yOU_40QhOABqDT-AjT2ZwZX1quEYeFGIqVJMLoOkyU1na9iX5KW8j4k16B8qwPHKiR1EclkA8RitpiyOfxN_30zZpyQ0cTfoRbf6Mx8N54CWobKI6KKcUV2BcIPQlXEomK5hLYDWFufGsrENAYoJtp_P0fYO-jUkpB5AIEOYtG13crlFppmXgzKIN_aubdOHUVlZwAMGpWbG_BP0P7fhBLrkrfCbw8KW9FAuN4p61h2R7SyCWOJ3g0TKIeRriNaOFo9xG8U5gUzA_tsQWQFSxZ6mCrXjkkf4c3fonodQevwLyP_cTCH48qBZWsrFI-837EJ4vY0r-vqPMnxAKn_ZsI4XewilOQPaNORtq4ybI4iWJlRsz1wsf3JA4lxqH0UXv9DP_C3oe_82009Xpwr_K95rk1RaBH0d7eEve1iYXRzTTHoSF4aWArLKqAK2boxqPxBvcHObb_KZ4HtccQXUXxrUJCM5dJlIc7w3mWx6KTsDXNNbBLItPKpzWn2cPq4CmR5p8DCcZ_5V9p