[assistant] `tests/src/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-javalite/4.26.0/src/test/java/com_google_protobuf/protobuf_javalite/SchemaUtilTest.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change:
[assistant] - Made the generated-style map default-entry holder and its `defaultEntry` field public:
[assistant]   - `LabelsDefaultEntryHolder`
[assistant]   - `defaultEntry`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Why:
[assistant] - In this test environment, protobuf’s `UnsafeUtil` may use an Android-style memory accessor because the Android `libcore.io.Memory` probe class is on the test runtime classpath.
[assistant] - That accessor reads static fields with `Field.get(null)` and returns `null` on `IllegalAccessException`.
[assistant] - Since the fixture is outside the `com.google.protobuf` package, a private/package-private holder field is not accessible to protobuf internals via that accessor.
[assistant] - Making the fixture holder and field public preserves the generated-code-style class name expected by `SchemaUtil.getMapDefaultEntry(...)` while avoiding the `mapDefaultEntry` null path.
